nodes.title: Required Custom Nodes
widgets_values:
✅ Please ensure these ComfyUI custom nodes are installed

Install (or update) each repo below into your ComfyUI/custom_nodes/ folder, then restart ComfyUI.

  1. pythongosssss / ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts
  2. yolain / ComfyUI-Easy-Use
  3. Kosinkadink / ComfyUI-VideoHelperSuite
  4. cubiq / ComfyUI_essentials
  5. banodoco / steerable-motion
  6. Fannovel16 / ComfyUI-Frame-Interpolation
  7. willmiao / ComfyUI-Lora-Manager
  8. Smirnov75 / ComfyUI-mxToolkit
  9. liusida / ComfyUI-AutoCropFaces
Quick install (git clone into ComfyUI/custom_nodes/)
cd /path/to/ComfyUI/custom_nodes
git clone https://github.com/pythongosssss/ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts
git clone https://github.com/yolain/ComfyUI-Easy-Use
git clone https://github.com/Kosinkadink/ComfyUI-VideoHelperSuite
git clone https://github.com/cubiq/ComfyUI_essentials
git clone https://github.com/banodoco/steerable-motion
git clone https://github.com/Fannovel16/ComfyUI-Frame-Interpolation
git clone https://github.com/willmiao/ComfyUI-Lora-Manager
git clone https://github.com/Smirnov75/ComfyUI-mxToolkit
git clone https://github.com/liusida/ComfyUI-AutoCropFaces
  • To update later: run git pull inside each repo folder.
  • After installing/updating, fully restart ComfyUI.

nodes.title: Crop Face
widgets_values:
🎯 Detect Faces & Focus on One

Set how many faces to detect, which one to focus on, and how the cropped image should appear.

  • number_of_faces — total number of faces to detect.
  • start_index — the starting position in the detected faces list (wraps around like a Python list).
  • scale_factor — adjusts how much padding is added around the face; 1 = no padding.
  • shift_factor — controls vertical face placement in the output: 0 = top, 0.5 = center, 1 = bottom.
  • max_faces_per_image — maximum number of faces to scan per image.
  • aspect_ratio — defines the crop ratio as width:height (e.g., 1:1 or 16:9).
💡 Tips
  • Increase scale_factor to include more background or context.
  • Adjust shift_factor to control how high or low the face appears.
  • Experiment with aspect_ratio to match different output formats.

nodes.title: Consistency Parameters
widgets_values:
🎭 Face Matching Parameters — Explanation

🧠 Face Match Weight

Controls how strongly the reference face influences the generated image. Higher values make the output more closely match the reference face, while lower values allow more creative variation.

⏱️ Start %

Specifies the point in the generation process (as a percentage) where the face-matching effect begins to take effect.

🏁 End %

Defines when the face-matching influence stops being applied during the generation process. Use this to fade out or limit the matching effect over time.

💡 Tip: Play around with the settings to suit your needs.
